Currently, GraalPy is attempting to support the full CPython runtime.

**CPython callbacks** refer to Python-wrapped C functions that return C-allocated memory back to the Python layer.

CPython itself runs correctly, but issues arise when running within the GraalVM environment.

One possible approach is to enable the VM to directly execute C and C++ libraries instead of replicating full CPython behavior.

## Issues
- Python callbacks
- Compatibility with C libraries in general
- Scale: the relevant libraries collectively contain millions of lines of code
